<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10683] Internal pagination of CQL index queries with compact storage is suboptimal</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10683</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The bug in page sizing logic for &lt;tt&gt;CompositesSearcher&lt;/tt&gt; described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8550&quot; title=&quot;Internal pagination in CQL3 index queries creating substantial overhead&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-8550&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-8550&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; also affects &lt;tt&gt;KeysSearcher&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
For any index with non-trivial cardinality, the page size tends to always be set suboptimally to 2, resulting in many more (smaller) slices being read the index table than necessary. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
